article.headline: SE Missouri 73, Tenn.-Martin 69
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Terrick Willoughby scored 14 points while Brandon Foust and Marcus Rhodes both added 12 to help Southeast Missouri edge past Tennessee-Martin 73-69 Saturday night. The Redhawks (9-15, 7-8 Ohio Valley Conference) were boosted by 20 points earned from turnovers, leading Tennessee-Martin 40-33 at the end of the first half. The Skyhawks (6-20, 4-12 OVC) tied the game six times and scored 36 points in the second half, beating Southeast Missouri's 33 points. Southeast Missouri's biggest lead was by 11 in the first half at 10:44, while Tennessee-Martin led by as much as two points late in the second half. It wasn't enough for the Skyhawks, despite four players racking up double-digit scores. McKale Jones was the leader with 14 points while Cleve Woodfork, Gerald Robinson and Joseph Bailey each contributed 13. Michael Rembert grabbed 10 rebounds for Southeast Missouri, matching 10 also made by Robinson.
